text: The Kempholey bubble-nest frog', rough-skinned frog, Rao's bush frog, or Kempholey leaping frog (Indirana longicrus) is a frog. It lives in India in the Western Ghat mountains. People have seen this frog 200 meters above sea level. Scientists think this frog probably lays eggs on wet rights, like other frogs in Indirana. Scientists think this frog might be in some danger from people cutting down trees to make farms. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Indirana longicrus
